Sao Tome and Principe’s Pinto da Costa Wins Presidential Runoff, AFP Says

-- B y   E m i l y   B o w e r s
-- 
2011-08-08T13:00:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/sao-tome-and-principe-s-pinto-da-costa-wins-presidential-runoff-afp-says.html
Manuel Pinto da Costa, who led Sao
Tome and Principe between 1975 and 1990, was elected as
president in a runoff election held yesterday, Agence-France
Presse reported, citing Victor Correia, head of the election
commission.  Pinto da Costa won 52.9 percent, defeating Evaristo
Carvalho, who received 47.1 percent, the  news agency  citing
Correia as saying. The results will be confirmed by the Atlantic
ocean islands’ Constitutional Court, the agency said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emily Bowers at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net  